    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-06-10T15:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-06-10T15:30:00-05:00" n="470"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.3715/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-10T16:00:00-04:30"
                            >June 10, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 11—12:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>668. My X–527, March 4, 1 p.m. Cuban Embassy inquires whether we can have a naval
                    vessel at Alicante June 16th to evacuate about 120 Cubans, three-fourths of whom
                    are expected to be women and children.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
